summary: you know that scene in Into the Spiderverse where New York City just stopped moving when the headlines about Spider-Man dying...
body: you know that scene in Into the Spiderverse where New York City just stopped moving when the headlines about Spider-Man dying broke? And everyone walking stopped in their tracks and stared at the news on their phones, and a city of strangers was unified in that moment of shock and grief? And then they attended a memorial in masses, wearing Spider-Man masks and shirts, all mourning a hero who they’d never truly met but it still felt like a personal loss for each in attendance? That’s what happened across the Earth in the mcu when the news of Tony’s death was released

blog.description: Formerly pirox2012. Just a small-town girl with big obsessions. Currently: Dr. Strange|TWD|Gilmore Girls|Marvel|The Mentalist|Star Wars|Star Trek|and just about a million other things that I can't think of at the moment. Thanks for visiting my humble blog.

summary: Y’all are gonna get so tired of me
body:
Y’all are gonna get so tired of me

But I can’t express just how much Robert Downey Jr. changed my life. Literally I would probably not be here alive and breathing if it hadn’t been for him. Yes, it became about the whole universe for me, but it all started with him. If I had never seen Iron Man, or if he had been played by someone else, my life would be totally different. I know it seems excessive to say I wouldn’t be here, but I absolutely adored RDJ in the movies. It truly gave me something to look forward to, to live for. I never had much going for me, and I probably would have given up on myself a long time ago. But I just had to see the next Iron Man or Avengers movie. So, I’m sorry if I annoy you with how much I have said this lately, but it is worth repeating. I love RDJ and I probably basically owe my life to him. He made me fall in love with something when I thought I was incapable. If I ever get to meet him, I will thank him for saving my life, because in my mind that’s exactly what happened. Thank you for being my hero ❤️

blog.name: gildedmuse
blog.title: Revolution Under Revision
blog.description:
She is an internet native trying to adjust to this whole "real world" trend. She is academically fangirlish (and fangirlishly academic when the occasional calls). She has a tendency towards being overly snarky yet total genuine when it matters, and when it matters you can expect a passionate, well researched defense that can get a bit wordy but always properly cited.

Oh, and she has a degree in English Lit and honestly misses all the essay writing.

Books/Literature: Dracula, Neil Gaiman, Allen Ginsberg, Mark Twain, Lemony Snicket, Chuck Palahniuk, Edgar Allen Poe, Brave New World, 1984, Kurt Vonnegut, Douglas Adams, Good Omens, Harry Potter, Old Man's War, Oscar Wilde, Tons Of Other Stuff

Film & Television: Pan's Labyrinth, Firefly, Buffy, Really Most Of Joss Whedon's Work, Parks & Rec, QI, Would I Lie To You?, Futurama, Inception, the MCU (and all of Marvel to some degree), Tons Of Other Stuff

Theater: Shakespeare, Arcadia, Cabaret, Hair, Rent, [Title Of Show], Drowsy Chaperone, Pajama Game, M. Butterfly, Wicked, Avenue Q, Dr. Horrible, Chess, The Last Five Years, Spelling Bee, Next To Normal, Songs For A New World, West Side Story, Spamalot, Reefer Madness, Just Tons Of Other Stuff
